File System Calculator Lab

*Objective*
Implement the Composite Design Pattern to build a file system representation. 
The goal is to create a structure where individual files and nested directories are treated uniformly, 
allowing you to calculate the total size of any folder regardless of its complexity.

Design Pattern: Composite
This lab utilizes the Composite Pattern to compose objects into tree structures to represent part-whole hierarchies.

Component: FileSystemItem

Leaf: File

Composite: Directory

*Instructions*
Interface Definition: Create the FileSystemItem interface with getName() and getSize() methods.

Leaf Implementation: Implement the File class to store a name and a fixed size in bytes.

Composite Implementation: Implement the Directory class. It should maintain a collection of FileSystemItem objects.

Recursive Calculation: The Directory.getSize() method must return the sum of all its contained items' sizes (recursively).

Build the Hierarchy: Create the following structure:

root

documents

report.pdf (2048 bytes)

notes.txt (512 bytes)

images

photo.jpg (4096 bytes)


Verification: Print the size of root, documents, and images to verify the recursive summation logic.


*Expected Output :Plaintext*

documents: 2560 bytes
images: 4096 bytes
root: 6656 bytes

Starter Code
Java

import java.util.*;

// Component interface
interface FileSystemItem {
    String getName();
    long getSize();  // Size in bytes
}

// Leaf: represents a file
class File implements FileSystemItem {
    private final String name;
    private final long size;
    
    public File(String name, long size) {
        this.name = name;
        this.size = size;
    }
    
    // TODO: Implement getName() and getSize()
}

// Composite: represents a directory
class Directory implements FileSystemItem {
    private final String name;
    private final List<FileSystemItem> contents = new ArrayList<>();
    
    public Directory(String name) {
        this.name = name;
    }
    
    public void add(FileSystemItem item) {
        contents.add(item);
    }
    
    // TODO: Implement getName() and getSize()
    // getSize() should recursively sum all contents
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // TODO: Build the structure and test
    }
}
